The decomposed body of a woman, who was reported missing more than a week ago, was found in a pit toilet in Qamata, Eastern Cape, police said on Friday. Captain Namhla Mdleleni said the 49-year-old woman was reported missing on December 20. Mdleleni said information led police to the house of the woman’s boyfriend, where her body was found. A 29-year-old man was arrested and appeared in the Cofimvaba Magistrate’s Court on a charge of murder. He is expected to appear in court again on January 8, 2019.